[{"count": 0, "tags": [], "creator": "joe.bissen@thieletech.com", "attachment_id": null, "is_private": false, "id": 61407, "time": "2004-07-30T21:31:08Z", "bug_id": 30418, "creation_time": "2004-07-30T21:31:08Z", "text": "The following bug occurs when precompiling jsp's following the instructions in\nthe Tomcat 5 documenation.\n\nFor the following line in the jsp, \n\n<a href=\"<c:out value=\"${item.feed.link}\"/>\"><c:out\nvalue=\"${item.feed.title}\"/></a> - <a href=\"<c:out\nvalue=\"${item.link}\"/>\"><c:out value=\"${item.title}\"/></a>\n\na source file is generated with the following :\n \n.....\nout.write(\"</a> \u00c2? <a href=\\\"\");\n.....\n\ninstead of \n......\nout.write(\"</a> \u00c2? <a href=\\\"\");\n......\n\nI tested other characters that the dash (colons and hyphens) and jasper2\ngenerates correct HTML, its just that it mistranslates the dash for some reason.\n\nThe problem does not occur if you allow Tomcat to compile pages on the fly while\nthe application is running.  Also, I never saw this issue with versions of\nTomcat 5 less than 5.0.25."}, {"count": 1, "tags": [], "bug_id": 30418, "attachment_id": null, "id": 61408, "creation_time": "2004-07-30T21:32:18Z", "time": "2004-07-30T21:32:18Z", "creator": "joe.bissen@thieletech.com", "text": "I meant that the source line expected is \n\nout.write(\"</a> - <a href=\\\"\");", "is_private": false}, {"count": 2, "attachment_id": null, "creator": "kin-man.chung@sun.com", "text": "I precompiled your JSP fragment, and got\n\n    out.write(\"</a> - <a href=\\\"\");\n\nas expected.\n\nIf you still have problem, please attach a test case (in war file), and\nbuild.xml for the precompilation.\n\nAlso, don't you want to escape the quotes inside quotes?", "id": 61471, "time": "2004-08-02T21:47:01Z", "bug_id": 30418, "creation_time": "2004-08-02T21:47:01Z", "tags": [], "is_private": false}]